This instruction is based on document: http://ashleynolan.co.uk/blog/launching-sublime-from-the-terminal

To install a sublime on Mac OS:
1. Go download the file
http://www.sublimetext.com/2

2. Double click the dmg file, then drag the sublime app to application folder.

3. Try you can open it correctly
open /Applications/Sublime\ Text\ 2.app/Contents/SharedSupport/bin/subl

4. Create a symlink, thus you can use it as a command just like using vim.
ln -s /Applications/Sublime\ Text\ 2.app/Contents/SharedSupport/bin/subl /usr/local/bin/sublime

5. open ~/.bash_profile file, if you don't have one, create one yourself, can put following line inside
export PATH=/usr/local/bin:$PATH

6. Try open a file by using: sublime xxx.java
